channel.title: Can't start Project files. Not able to make new project
channel.description:
I have one old project in 4.21 and I have a newer mod in 4.22.3. For some strange reason, I can't load it in, It wants to me rebuild everything when I already did that last summer when I started on the mod. This year it asked me to do it again. So I downloaded the project starter files again and tried to start a new project. Same thing. It wants me to compile the source by name. I didn't know how to do that so I loaded up VS 2019 and tried to compile it. Well, I got plugins missing errors and so on.
So the question is how do I get my project to load in. I'm all so on the mod support discord.
